For bullish mitigation, when price crosses above the upper boundary, the midpoint box top aligns with the FVG upper box top, the FVG upper box bottom also aligns, and any existing text is cleared before the FVG is removed.

When `_h > b_UB` and `_l < t_UB` with `_p == false`, the bearish case begins. If the high enters the FVG from below (`_h < t_UB`), the midpoint bottom gets updated to the maximum of the high and the current midpoint top, while the FVG upper box bottom adjusts accordingly.

When price crosses above the FVG entirely (`_h >= t_UB`), the boxes are reset to remove the FVG structure. The right edges of all boxes align to the current bar index, and the line extends to match. The percentage calculation compares the adjusted midpoint range against the FVG boundaries to determine the mitigation depth.

